== Linear system determined by a map to a projective space ==

Each morphism from an algebraic variety to a projective space determines a base-point-free linear system on the variety; because of this, a base-point-free linear system and a map to a projective space are often used interchangeably.

For a closed immersion formula_122 of algebraic varieties there is a pullback of a linear system formula_123 on formula_2 to formula_125, defined as formula_126 (page 158).

=== O(1) on a projective variety ===
A projective variety formula_2 embedded in formula_128 has a natural linear system determining a map to projective space from formula_129. This sends a point formula_130 to its corresponding point formula_131.

